==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Arterialization
<hw>Ar*te`ri*al*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The process of converting venous blood into
arterial blood during its passage through the lungs, oxygen being
absorbed and carbonic acid evolved; -- called also
<altname>a⟦eum⟧ration</altname> and
<altname>hematosis</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arterialize</ent>⟦br⟧
